overview: Meet Kayla Gore, a force of nature in her native Memphis community. After facing homelessness, assault, discrimination and her own HIV status after coming out as trans, Kayla knows firsthand what it will take to change the sobering survival statistics about HIV in the trans community. Today she's making that mission her own - through her non profit organization that builds and awards - for free - tiny houses to trans people in the Memphis community.
title: Blind Angels: Memphis, TN
